### [Psalms Chapter 145](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#001.md)

[Psalms 145:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">psa 145:1</span></span>

A Psalm of praise to God for His mighty, righteous, and gracious
government of all men, and of His humble and suffering people in
particular. (Psa. 145:1-21)

(Compare [Psa 30:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa030.htm#001).md).

bless thy name--celebrate Thy perfections ([Psa
5:11](../../../bib/kjv/psa005.htm#011).md). God is addressed as king,
alluding to His government of men.

[Psalms 145:3](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">psa 145:3</span></span>

(Compare [Psa 18:3](../../../bib/kjv/psa018.htm#003.md); [Psa
48:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa048.htm#001).md).

greatness--as displayed in His works.

[Psalms 145:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">psa 145:4</span></span>

shall declare--literally, "they shall declare," that is, all
generations.

[Psalms 145:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">psa 145:5</span></span>

I will speak--or, "muse" ([Psa 77:12](../../../bib/kjv/psa077.htm#012.md);
[Psa 119:15](../../../bib/kjv/psa119.htm#015).md).

thy wondrous works--or, "words of thy wonders," that is, which described
them ([Psa 105:27](../../../bib/kjv/psa105.htm#027), Margin.md).

[Psalms 145:6](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">psa 145:6</span></span>

terrible acts--which produce dread or fear.

[Psalms 145:7](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">psa 145:7</span></span>

memory-- ([Psa 6:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa006.htm#005).md), remembrance, or
what causes to be remembered.

righteousness--as in [Psa 143:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa143.htm#001.md),
goodness according to covenant engagement.

[Psalms 145:8](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">psa 145:8</span></span>

(Compare [Psa 103:8](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#008.md); [Psa
111:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa111.htm#004).md).

over all, &c.--rests on all His works.

[Psalms 145:10](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">psa 145:10</span></span>

bless--as in [Psa 145:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#001.md), to praise
with reverence, more than merely to praise.

[Psalms 145:11](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">psa 145:11</span></span>

The declaration of God's glory is for the extension of His knowledge and
perfections in the world.

[Psalms 145:13](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">psa 145:13</span></span>

(Compare [Dan 4:3](../../../bib/kjv/dan004.htm#003.md), [Dan
4:34](../../../bib/kjv/dan004.htm#034).md).

[Psalms 145:14](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">psa 145:14</span></span>

(Compare [Psa 37:17](../../../bib/kjv/psa037.htm#017.md); [Psa
54:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa054.htm#004).md).

[Psalms 145:15](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#015.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_015">psa 145:15</span></span>

eyes of . . . thee--or, look with expecting faith ([Psa
104:27-28](../../../bib/kjv/psa104.htm#027).md).

[Psalms 145:17](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">psa 145:17</span></span>

holy . . . works--literally, "merciful" or "kind, goodness" ([Psa
144:2](../../../bib/kjv/psa144.htm#002).md) is the corresponding noun.

righteous--in a similar relation of meaning to "righteousness" ([Psa
145:7](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#007).md).

[Psalms 145:18](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#018.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_018">psa 145:18</span></span>

(Compare [Psa 34:7](../../../bib/kjv/psa034.htm#007.md), [Psa
34:10](../../../bib/kjv/psa034.htm#010).md).

[Psalms 145:20](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">psa 145:20</span></span>

Those who fear Him ([Psa 145:19](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#019).md) are
those who are here said to love Him.

[Psalms 145:21](../../../bib/kjv/psa145.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">psa 145:21</span></span>

(Compare [Psa 33:21](../../../bib/kjv/psa033.htm#021).md).

all flesh-- ([Psa 65:2](../../../bib/kjv/psa065.htm#002).md). The Psalm
ends, as it began, with ascriptions of praise, in which the pious will
ever delight to join.

